The health fraternity in Lesotho is reeling from the loss of a medical giant. Dr. Mmusi Mokete boasted an illustrious career spanning over 40 years and was bestowed accolades of the highest honour even from His Majesty the King. He served as an ophthalmologist, lived a simple life dedicating most of his resources to assisting young doctors and developed the health sector in Lesotho. For more on the story, watch the video below: 